    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-07-27T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-07-27T16:00:00-05:00" n="96"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/7–2750: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Deputy Representative on the North Atlantic
                        Council</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spofford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-07-27T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 27, 1950—10 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Depto1">Depto</gloss> 16. Report of third session<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d96fn1">Third meeting, first session.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_NAC1">NAC</gloss> Deputies follows: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Continued discussion agenda item 6. <list>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Alphand proposed provisional financing arrangements to start
                                    production of staple military items. Long-term plans would
                                    require pooling of expenses in light each country’s financial
                                    situation, social conditions, and ability contribute.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                                <item>US introduced proposal reported <gloss target="#t_Depto1"
                                        >Depto</gloss> 15, July 27 stressing desirability using
                                    existing <gloss target="#t_NAT1">NAT</gloss> machinery to
                                    expedite immediate increase in production priority items, and,
                                    in event complete agreement could not be reached by other <gloss
                                        target="#t_NAT1">NAT</gloss> agencies within deadlines set,
                                    issues would at least be sharply defined for decision by
                                    deputies or <gloss target="#t_NAC1">NAC</gloss>
                                </item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Several times Alphand urged studies should cover physical
                                    production capacity and mechanism for use of funds available in
                                    US as well as Europe. Spoke in terms of common <gloss
                                        target="#t_NAT1">NAT</gloss> budget to meet common
                                    requirements of <gloss target="#t_NAT1">NAT</gloss> forces,
                                    implying US production facilities and US funds should be
                                    available for production as determined by <gloss
                                        target="#t_NAT1">NAT</gloss> authorities.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Spofford pointed out present need was to put unused production
                                    capacity in Europe to use, US already fully using production
                                    capacity and converting from civilian uses, and large part US
                                    production being made available to Europe through <gloss
                                        target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss>.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">e</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Alphand proposed Military Committee also indicate priority
                                    infrastructure projects for immediate implementation. Supported
                                    by UK. Spofford pointed out complications in defining
                                    infrastructure and suggested question would need longer study
                                    than possible within proposed timetable.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">f</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Belgium proposed that, in view long stalemate in type of
                                    coordinated planning proposed by US, deputies must reach
                                    agreement on paragraph 3(<hi rend="italic">d</hi>) <gloss
                                        target="#t_Depto1">Depto</gloss> 15 (financing mechanism)
                                    before further action profitable. Spofford remarked action in
                                    all agencies should proceed concurrently and experts should be
                                    asked study technical, financial matters involved.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">g</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Replying to question how US proposal fitted in with studies
                                    requested <gloss target="#t_Depcirctel1">Depcirtel</gloss> July
                                    22, Spofford said latter was US request for broad indication of
                                    European military effort in future, former was US suggestion get
                                    immediate production under way through use <gloss
                                        target="#t_NAT1">NAT</gloss> agencies. Two projects not
                                    inconsistent or conflicting.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">h</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Deputies agreed reach final decision on US proposal at meeting
                                    afternoon July 28. Chairman <gloss target="#t_PWS1"
                                        >PWS</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_MPSB1">MPSB</gloss>
                                    authorized inform <gloss target="#t_PWS1">PWS</gloss> of
                                    proposal at meeting morning July 28 without prejudice to final
                                    deputies action.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <pb facs="0170" n="148" xml:id="pg_148"/>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Deputies agreed recess after Friday meeting until Tuesday, giving time
                            to consult governments.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>No communiqué issued.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Department <gloss target="#t_Depto1">Depto</gloss> 16, repeated Paris info
                    148. Department pass Secretary Defense.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Spofford</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
